# Coding consists of 3 steps: Writing, Executing (or running), Fixing errors (or debugging)
# Even experienced programmers get coding errors (or bugs) all the time. So if you're making mistakes, it's ok! You're on the right track.
# Even the tiniest typo or a misplaced tab in your code will result in an error.
# Bugs are an expected part of writing code. The rick to being a good coder is staying cool when dealing  with bugs.
# If your code contains multiple bugs, you need to fix all of them for the code to be executed correctly.
# The computer reads and executeds instructions line by ilne, from top to bottom. The execution of the program will be interrupted at the first error encountered.